12/12/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Ivica Dacic was unanimously re-elected as leader of the Socialist Party of Serbia (SPS) at the eighth party congress in Belgrade on Saturday (December 11th). Dacic, who also serves as deputy prime minister and interior minister, said that SPS has gone through major reformation to become a modern leftist party. The party, he added, has made "a radical break with the past" and is committed to achieving the goal of EU membership. (Tanjug, RTS - 11/12/10)
